-- U.K. Quantitative Funds Increase on Bonds, Currencies, Financial Times Sa
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-10-13T04:54:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/u-k-quantitative-funds-increase-on-bonds-currencies-financial-times-sa.html
Quantitative hedge-fund firms such
as U.K.-based Winton Capital Management Ltd., BlueCrest Capital
Management Ltd. and  Man Group Plc  are experiencing a surge in
returns as a result of moves in currency and bond markets, the
Financial Times reported.  The boom has lasted two months and is heading for a third,
the newspaper said.  Man Group’s AHL, one of the biggest single funds at $21
billion, has gained 8.22 percent so far this month and 17.95
percent since January, the FT said, citing an unidentified
person familiar with the matter.  Winton Capital’s $16 billion fund had gained 10.13 percent
by the end of September and is up another 2 percent this month;
BlueCrest Capital’s $11.4 billion BlueTrend quantitative fund
has returned 8.34 percent so far this year, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alan Purkiss  in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
